SIMPLE: numerical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Numerical
<hw>Nu*mer"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>num⟦eacute⟧rique</ets>. See <er>Number</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Belonging to number; denoting number; consisting in
numbers; expressed by numbers, and not letters; <as>as,
<ex>numerical</ex> characters; a <ex>numerical</ex> equation; a
<ex>numerical</ex> statement.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Numerical</xex>, as opposed to
<contr>algebraical</contr>, is used to denote a value irrespective of
its sign; thus, -5 is numerically greater than -3, though algebraically
less.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The same in number; hence, identically the same;
identical; <as>as, the same <ex>numerical</ex> body</as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Would to God that all my fellow brethren, which with me bemoan the
loss of their books, . . . might rejoice for the recovery thereof,
though not the same <qex>numerical</qex> volumes.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>relating to or having ability to think in or work
with numbers; <as>as, tests for rating <ex>numerical</ex> aptitude</as>.
Contrasted with <ant>verbal</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mathematical.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Numerical equation</b></col> <fld>(Alg.)</fld>, <cd>an
equation which has all the quantities except the unknown expressed in
numbers; -- distinguished from <contr>literal equation</contr>.</cd> --
<col><b>Numerical value</b></col> <cd>of an equation or expression, that
deduced by substituting numbers for the letters, and
reducing.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Numeric</ent>⟦br⟧
